dance and solo singing at the Modern School of Music of Thessaloniki (Σύγχρονο Ωδείο Θεσσαλονίκης).[5] She has played in and directed many theater plays in Greece and presented books from modern Greek literature authors in literary salons.[6] Her last stage performance has taken place in Larissa in 2015. Work[edit] Stage[edit]   2014: Κούκλες by Ioanna Fotiadou (English: Dolls. Director and actress.)[7] 2010: Πάθη στο κόκκινο (English: Passions in red. Producer, director, actress) 2010: 19 Γυναίκες σε μία φωνή (English: 19 Women in one voice. Actress, singer)    2011, 2013: Μαύρα Τριαντάφυλλα (English: Black Roses. Producer, director, actress) Bear and an other jazz story.  Radio[edit] Chrisoula Christou is the producer of the weekly radio show Mousikes Istories (Μουσικές Ιστορίες) on the station Dimotiko Radiofono Larissas.[citation needed] External links[edit]  Interview onscene.eu Pathi sto kokkino, Eleftheria Newspaper Nineteen women in one voice, Eleftheria Newspaper  References[edit]   ^ http://www.press-gr.com/2010/10/blog-post_6460.html ^ http://www.larissanet.gr/2014/02/02/xr-xristou-pote-den-einai-arga-gia-n-allaxoume/ ^ http://www.onlarissa.gr/2014/01/30/i-parastasi-koukles-sto-stage/ ^ http://www.tragadramaschool.gr/ ^ http://synodeio.wix.com/soth ^ http://www.larissanet.gr/2014/02/02/xr-xristou-pote-den-einai-arga-gia-n-allaxoume/ ^ http://www.onlarissa.gr/2014/01/24/premiera-gia-to-theatriko-ergo-koukles-sto-stage/                      Retrieved from "https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Chrisoula_Christou&oldid=725485515"          Categories: People from Larissa1962 birthsLiving peopleGreek actressesHidden categories: Articles with topics of unclear notability from April 2015All articles with topics of unclear notabilityArticles lacking reliable references from April 2015All articles lacking reliable referencesBLP articles lacking sources from April 2015Orphaned articles from April 2015All orphaned articlesArticles with hCardsAll articles with u